ic and philosophy, one that describes rhetoric as more than a matter of effective communication and recasts persuasion as a philosophical concern central to notions of human subjectivity. Ultimately, Kastely insists, persuasion enables us to love the world appropriately.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aPersuasion (Rhetoric). 0aRhetoricxPhilosophy. 0aSubjectivity. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh  apersuasion, subjectivity, Eros, tragedy, sameness, difference, Freud, reconstitution, rhetoric, Plato.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076650940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226822112423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226822112/original  a978-3-11-076650-9  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles